# Category Module — Implementation Constraints

**Status:** Approved design — implement on `develop` only.

## Do NOT modify

- Contacts module (frozen): Supplier, Customer, contacts services/migrations/UI
- Product Controls module (frozen): controls, control groups, `CTL-`/`CTG-` services/migrations/UI
- Product Catalog navigation, menus, routes, sidebar, or other submenu pages
- `config/agricart.php` module structure (only extend `Categories` page)

## UI reference

Match Contacts module exactly for list pages:

- Single-row toolbar: Search → primary filters → More Filters → Add (far right)
- Modal CRUD (7XL), View/Edit/Move/Archive/Restore actions
- No bulk actions in v1
- Reuse toolbar CSS pattern (`contacts-list-toolbar` / `categories-list-toolbar`)

## Database relationships — CRITICAL

Use **only** `id` and `parent_id` for tree relationships, FKs, joins, and lookups.

**Never** use `visual_mapping_code` for:

- Foreign keys
- Joins
- Lookups
- Business logic
- Eloquent relationships

`visual_mapping_code` is display/reporting only.

## Permanent identifiers

| Field | Rule |
|-------|------|
| `category_number` (`CAT-000001`) | **Immutable** — never changes on move, archive, edit, or any operation |
| `visual_mapping_code` | May change **only** when hierarchy location changes (move) |
| `sort_order` | Permanent sibling slot — **no renumbering** when siblings are archived |

## Move operation — CRITICAL

- **Always** wrap in `DB::transaction()`
- Update moved node + entire subtree: `parent_id`, `level`, `full_path`, `visual_mapping_code`, `is_leaf`
- Preserve: `category_number`, image, descriptions, SEO, HS, usage, AI fields, `products_count`, product FKs
- New parent must be `status = active`
- Block move to self or descendant
- Must be reversible via normal Edit/Move UI — no manual DB fixes

## Archive stability

- Archiving does **not** change visual mapping codes
- Archiving does **not** renumber sibling codes
- Cannot create or move categories under archived parents

## Field rules

- `name_en`: required (NOT NULL)
- `name_ur`: optional at entry (stored as empty string until AI enrichment); NOT NULL column
- `slug`: nullable, unique when set — AI-generated after enrichment
- `ai_status`: defaults to `pending` on create; values: pending, processing, complete, review, failed
- `search_terms`, `faqs_en`, `faqs_ur`: JSON nullable — AI-managed structured content
- `is_leaf`: system-managed only — never exposed in create/edit forms
- `products_count`: denormalized, required for list/reporting
- Default list sort: `visual_mapping_code` ASC (hierarchy order), not `created_at` desc

## Schema status

**FROZEN** as of migration `2026_06_25_100001_add_category_content_and_ai_fields_to_categories_table`.

Deferred to storefront/marketplace phase: `structured_data_json`, `google_product_category_id`, `marketplace_status`.

## Visual mapping depth letters

| Level | Letter |
|-------|--------|
| 0 | R |
| 1 | M |
| 2 | S |
| 3 | C |
| 4 | L |
| 5+ | N per depth |

## Scalability

Adjacency list (`parent_id`) + indexed columns must support unlimited tree depth without schema redesign.
